article.headline: San Jose St. 80, Cal Poly 63
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Freshman Darion Goins hit four 3-pointers while scoring 16 points as San Jose State finally got its first victory of the season, 80-63 over Cal Poly on Sunday. Tim Pierce added 12 points for the Spartans (1-6), who rolled to a nine-point halftime lead and coasted to the victory while hitting 11 3-pointers in their home opener. San Jose State had opened coach George Nessman's second season with six road games, including local losses to Santa Clara and Saint Mary's earlier in the week. Dawin Whiten and Tyler McGinn scored 11 points apiece for the Mustangs (4-3), whose three-game winning streak was snapped. Cal Poly was outrebounded 43-23 and committed 14 turnovers.
